        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-8 justify-content-center">
                <p class="to-fill">Le Raisin is a restaurant’s web site. The goal was to present the restaurant to customers and create a tool for the owner to update his weekly menus.</p>
                <p class="to-fill">I took this job as a challenge for myself. I started learning web programming and wanted to work on a project with real constraints, not just something I do for myself but a product for a client, answering his needs with all the problematics that come with.</p>
                <p class="to-fill">It was a segemented 3 months project. I started working on the design and had to wait for the owner’s approval, having difficulties with the restaurant’s oppening we had to postpone the website’s development for a few months The programming part took a few weeks, it was a side project during the development of Bokida.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <!--MY TASKS-->
    <div class="section">
        <div class="row justify-content-center section-title">
            <div class="col-3 align-self-center divider"></div>
            <div class="col-lg-4">
                <h2 class="to-fill">My Tasks</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="col-3 align-self-center divider"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <h3 class="to-fill">UX Design</h3>
                <p class="to-fill">The graphical charter having been done by my sister previously I already had the branding and the logo. I have been able to concentrate on the UX. I used Adobe Illustrator to create my wireframes and mockups.</p>
                <h4 class="to-fill">Visitor Side</h4>
                <p class="to-fill">My goal was to create a one page web site with everything available easily and a clean look. My biggest constraint was my technical skills that I tried to turn to my advantage. I used a simple layout with tabs organized by section. The most important part was the « Menu » section where the user could find the lunch formula, the dishes, suggestions and the wines. Each of thoses sub section has a different layout.</p>
                <h4 class="to-fill">Admin Side</h4>
                <p class="to-fill">Concerning the admin side I mostly needed to do something functional and easy to use as it would only be used by the owner and the cook. They needed to be able to update the lunch formula, the dishes and the suggestions.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="col-lg-5">
                <h3 class="to-fill">Programming</h3>
                <p class="to-fill">I used Bootstrap as a base for the CSS and did everything else from scratch (cf. What I Would Do Differently).</p>
                <p class="to-fill">I wrote everything in HTML and JS except for my API that I wrote in PHP which was at the time the only server side language I knew. I chose JS instead of PHP for the dynamic content for its comfort in use for the user.</p>
                <img height="128 px" width="100%" src="/images/RAISIN_370-128.png">
            </div>
        </div>
