            </div>
            <div class="col-2 align-self-center divider"></div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-7">
                <p class="to-fill">I would use a framework or a library to simplify server requests and compatibility issues such as Angular, React or Vue. I really enjoy coding with JS and in the future I would like to learn more tools using this language.</p>    
                <p class="to-fill">On the design side I would now go for a bolder design while keeping the clean and simple look. I would use bigger titles, more spacing between sections, get rid of the carousel. I would also take  the pictures myself to get a better quality and, knowing where they would go, be more pertinent.</p>
                <p class="to-fill">For my next web project I would use prototyping software better suited for web design than Illustrator such as Axure RP, Pencil or InVision. Illustrator is good to test different layouts rapidly but offers no features to test navigation and interactivity.</p>
